+Mini-App Development Plan: Triks – In-Game Loot Exchange
+1. Project Overview
+
+Triks is a lightweight application designed to allow gamers to exchange in-game loot across various titles. The main goal is to create a fast, secure, and user-friendly platform where users can list items, browse available loot, and trade with others in real time.
+
+2. Core Features
+2.1 User Accounts & Profiles
+
+Email / Google / Steam login
+
+Profile pages with:
+
+Username
+
+Linked game accounts
+
+Reputation / rating system
+
+Trade history
+
+2.2 Loot Listing System
+
+Add new items with:
+
+Game selection
+
+Item name
+
+Rarity
+
+Description
+
+Screenshots (optional)
+
+Edit or delete listings
+
+Automatic item status (available / traded)
+
+2.3 Search & Filtering
+
+Filter by game, rarity, item type
+
+Keyword search
+
+Sort by newest, most wanted, popularity
+
+2.4 Trading Mechanism
+
+Send trade offers
+
+Chat between traders
+
+Trade confirmation system
+
+Optional escrow system to prevent scams
+
+2.5 Notifications
+
+New messages
+
+Incoming trade offers
+
+Trade status updates
+
+2.6 Security & Anti-Scam Tools
+
+Account verification
+
+Reporting system
+
+User reputation scoring
+
+Optional 2FA
+
+3. Technical Architecture
+3.1 Frontend
+
+Framework: React, Vue, or Flutter (for mobile)
+
+UI components:
+
+Item cards
+
+Filter panels
+
+Chat window
+
+Responsive design for mobile and desktop
+
+3.2 Backend
+
+Language: Node.js, Python (FastAPI/Django), or Go
+
+Key modules:
+
+Authentication
+
+Database models
+
+Trading logic
+
+Chat engine (WebSockets)
+
+3.3 Database
+
+MongoDB or PostgreSQL
+
+Collections / tables:
+
+Users
+
+Items
+
+Trades
+
+Messages
+
+Reports
+
+3.4 APIs
+
+REST or GraphQL
+
+Optional game-account integration (Steam API, etc.)
+
+4. Development Stages
+Stage 1 — Planning & Design
+
+Define item models, user flow, and UI wireframes
+
+Select technologies and tools
+
+Stage 2 — Core Architecture Setup
+
+Backend project setup
+
+Database schema creation
+
+Frontend boilerplate
+
+Stage 3 — Feature Development
+
+User authentication
+
+Item listing and browsing
+
+Search & filters
+
+Trade system
+
+Notifications
+
+Stage 4 — Testing
+
+Unit tests
+
+UI/UX testing
+
+Security and penetration testing
+
+Stage 5 — Deployment
+
+Deploy backend to cloud (AWS / Render / DigitalOcean)
+
+Deploy frontend (Vercel / Netlify)
+
+Connect domain: triks.app (optional)
+
+Stage 6 — Post-Launch
+
+Collect user feedback
+
+Add premium features (skins marketplace, advanced filters, etc.)
+
+5. Monetization Options (Optional)
+
+Premium accounts (priority listings)
+
+Small transaction fees
+
+Ads (in non-intrusive areas)
+
+Subscription for extra features
